"Chlela F., Husaunndee A., Inard C., Riederer P.","A new methodology for the design of low energy buildings",2009,"Energy and Buildings","41","9",,"982","990",,,10.1016/j.enbuild.2009.05.001,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-67649202171&partnerID=40&md5=5d00eba668e1b687d376a0a67233dd22","Centre Scientifique et Technique du Bâtiment (CSTB), 84 avenue Jean Jaurès, 77421 Marne-la-Vallée, France; Veolia Environnement R and D, 291 Avenue Dreyfous Ducas, 78520 Limay, France; LEPTIAB, University of La Rochelle, Av. Michel Crépeau, 17042 La Rochelle, France","Chlela, F., Centre Scientifique et Technique du Bâtiment (CSTB), 84 avenue Jean Jaurès, 77421 Marne-la-Vallée, France; Husaunndee, A., Veolia Environnement R and D, 291 Avenue Dreyfous Ducas, 78520 Limay, France; Inard, C., LEPTIAB, University of La Rochelle, Av. Michel Crépeau, 17042 La Rochelle, France; Riederer, P., Centre Scientifique et Technique du Bâtiment (CSTB), 84 avenue Jean Jaurès, 77421 Marne-la-Vallée, France","The Kyoto protocol binded the developed countries to reduce the greenhouse gas emissions at least by 5% by 2008-2012 in order to tackle global warming and climate change. Some of the measures of the governments to achieve this goal are to promote new buildings construction and to retrofit existing buildings while satisfying low energy criteria. This means improving energy efficiency of buildings and energy systems, developing sustainable building concepts and promoting renewable energy sources. The design of a low energy building requires parametric studies via simulation tools in order to optimize the design of the building envelope and HVAC systems. These studies are often complex and time consuming due to a large number of parameters to consider. Hence, this paper aims to set up a methodology that simplifies parametrical studies during the design process of a low energy building. The methodology is based on the Design of Experiments (DOE) method which is a statistical method widely used in industry to perform parametric studies that reduces the required number of experiments. © 2009 Elsevier B.V. All rights reserved.","Buildings design methodology; Design of Experiments method; Low energy buildings; Numerical simulation tools; Parametrical studies","Building envelopes; Design of Experiments method; Design of experiments methods; Design process; Developed countries; Energy systems; Existing building; HVAC system; KYOTO protocol; Low energies; Low energy buildings; Numerical simulation tools; Parametric study; Parametrical studies; Renewable energy source; Simulation tool; Sustainable building; Climatology; Computer simulation; Design of experiments; Electric fault location; Emission control; Energy efficiency; Gas emissions; Global warming; Greenhouse gases; Intelligent buildings; Leakage (fluid); Retrofitting; Tools; Renewable energy resources",,,,,,"Thomsen, K.E., Schultz, J.M., Poel, B., Measured performance of 12 demonstration projects. IEA Task 13 ""advanced solar low energy buildings"" (2005) Energy and Buildings, 37 (2), pp. 111-119; Wolfgang, F., Schnieders, J., Dorer, V., Haas, A., Re-inventing air heating: convenient and comfortable within the frame of the Passive House concept (2005) Energy and Buildings, 37 (11), pp. 1186-1203; http://www.prebat.net, CSTB, Comparaison internationale bâtiment et énergie, Available on:, 2006Pillet, M., (1999) Les plans d'expérience par la méthode de Taguchi, , Les Editions d'Organisation; Goupy, J., (1999) Plan d'expériences pour surfaces de réponses, , Editions Dunod; Goupy, J., Modélisation par les plans d'expériences (2000) Techniques de l'Ingénieur, R275; Fang, K.T., Runze, L., Sudjianto, A., (2006) Design and Modelling for Computer Experiments, , Computer Science and Data Analysis Series, Chapman & Hall/CRC; Anthony, J., (2003) Design of Experiments for Engineers and Scientist, , Butterworth Heinemann; Ghosh, S., Rao, C.R., (1996) Handbook of Statistics, 13. , Elsevier; Khattree, R., Rao, C.